<td><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000">about the charm spell</font></td></tr></table></td></tr></table><p><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER" bgcolor="000000">
<tr>
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" align="CENTER">
<tr bgcolor="999999">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td width="10"><img src="http://www.maximumeq.com/forum/Images/SmallNew.gif" border="0" alt="New Message"></td><td width="50%"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>Charm (modified 0 times)</b> </font></td><td width="50%" align="RIGHT"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>Quillien</b></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Well, personally I love enchanters.  I played a magician until 35, and I loved it also, but it wasn't nearly as fun as my enchanter.  Anyway, about charm.<p>

Well, enchanters are the ONLY class that can solo 2 reds, or a yellow and a red at the same time.  This works especially well outside, with sow, and its AWESOME with clarity.  Basically, you find something to kill, preferably not red, and tashan it.  Then run, and charm it.  Go back and attack another creature with it.  Make sure your pet is winning, and meditate.  Whenever charm runs out, run out of range, then recharm.  Continue until your pet kills the other, then either wait for charm to run out, or invis yourself.  Finish off the VERY hurt monster, and there you go, 2 yellow or higher things dead solo.  Thats worth 1/4 of a bar of exp or more.  <p>

I think charm is a great spell, and although it is not useful at all times, it can make soloing possibly and even very good exp.<p>

Of coure, a very high charmisma is very useful in doing this, since it makes charm nearly never resisted, and makes it last longer.<p>

Quillien, 26 enchanter of Lanys T'Vyl</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
